{"issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/7696", "repo": "rails", "body": "Yeah, I'm gonna say that I'm personally a :-1: on this feature; I think that in general, if you had done the 'right thing,' which is `if Rails.env.test? || Rails.env.cucumber?`, this wouldn't have happened, but also, the `=` vs `==` thing is a very common bug.\n\nThat said, currently, this has no tests, which would be needed in order to get it accepted as well. Or documentation. But I wouldn't bother writing stuff until someone from core actually reviews this.", "_id": {"$oid": "523dd072bd354364b900a62d"}, "issue_id": 7696, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/8684281", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/7696#issuecomment-8684281", "updated_at": "2012-09-19T08:36:16Z", "user": {"subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik/subscriptions", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik/events{/privacy}", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik/repos", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik/gists{/gist_id}", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik", "login": "steveklabnik", "gravatar_id": "233c279c012ebac792aaa805f966cbc7", "html_url": "https://github.com/steveklabnik", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik/following{/other_user}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik/received_events", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik/orgs", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/233c279c012ebac792aaa805f966cbc7?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F0c22d45f31acf0f4192c8c12b7a55dee.png", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "id": 27786, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik/followers", "type": "User"}, "created_at": "2012-09-19T08:36:16Z", "id": 8684281, "owner": "rails"}
